The article mentions several appointments and reappointments of individuals to various positions in the United States government. Some of the appointments include Thomas G. Day as Commissioner of the Postal Regulatory Commission, Basil Ivanhoe Gooden as Under Secretary of Agriculture for Rural Development, Colleen Danielle Holland as United States District Judge for the Western District of New York, John A. Kazen as United States District Judge for the Southern District of Texas, Colleen Duffy Kiko as a Member of the Federal Labor Relations Authority, Ramona Villagomez Manglona as Judge for the District Court for the Northern Mariana Islands, Patrice J. Robinson as a Member of the Board of Directors of the Tennessee Valley Authority, and Micah W.J. Smith as United States District Judge for the District of Hawaii.